**Figure 5:** *(Top-left)* Duration distribution showing stark 2.5x difference between yes (mean 553s) and no (mean 221s) subscribers. *(Top-right)* Contact count vs subscription rate showing optimal range at 1-2 contacts (~15%), declining thereafter. *(Middle-left)* Previous campaign outcome impact—success yields 60%+ repeat subscription. *(Middle-right)* Monthly performance with March peaking at 47%, May lowest at 7%. *(Bottom-left)* Day-of-week patterns showing relatively uniform distribution. *(Bottom-right)* Scatter plot of campaign contacts vs duration colored by outcome, illustrating that successful calls cluster in low-contact, high-duration region.

