**Age × Economic Interaction:**

| Age Group | Low Euribor (<2%) | High Euribor (>4%) | Economic Sensitivity |
|-----------|-------------------|--------------------|--------------------|
| Young (18-30) | 16% | 9% | 1.78x |
| Middle (31-55) | 12% | 7% | 1.71x |
| **Senior (56+)** | **27%** | **14%** | **1.93x** |

**Key Finding:** Senior customers are most economically sensitive—conversion nearly doubles in low vs high Euribor environments (27% vs 14%). This suggests **timing campaigns for senior segments based on economic forecasts** can yield significant improvements.

**Duration × Economy Correlation:**

In favorable economic periods (low Euribor, high confidence):
- Average call duration: 488 seconds (yes) vs 235 seconds (no)  
- Ratio: 2.08x

In unfavorable periods:
- Average call duration: 612seconds (yes) vs 208 seconds (no)
- Ratio: 2.94x

**Interpretation:** During economic downturns, convincing customers requires even longer calls, suggesting increased resistance. Campaign efficiency suffers in poor economic conditions not only through lower conversion but also through higher time investment per conversion.

